svg.title: A map showing from top to bottom a body of water marked with the word “River,” a slough coming into the river, a creek that goes into the slough and two roads crossing each other. A small square indicates the presence of a building located between the crossroads and the creek. An X mark is placed to the right of the building, touching the crooked line that represents the creek, accompanied by the text “2–3 miles, Greenland.” To the left of the building is an arrow or direction marker pointing north.
